⚙️ Guidance to the Reader: How to Use the Principles

This is not just theory. This guidance block instructs how the reader (a Delivery Manager, QA Lead, or PM) must actively apply these principles in day-to-day decisions:
	1.	Interpret, Don’t Obey
	•	When a process doesn’t suit the context, ask: Which principle is at risk?
	•	You may adapt form, but not essence.
	2.	Invoke Principles During Escalations
	•	If a stakeholder pushes a request that bypasses quality, respond: “That conflicts with our evidence-over-opinion principle — let’s show the trade-off.”
	•	Use principles as allies, not sermons.
	3.	Test New Practices Against Principles
	•	Before adopting a new dashboard, governance step, or tool — check: does it promote transparency, alignment, accountability?
	•	If not, reject or adjust.
	4.	Teach Principles to the Team and Stakeholders
	•	Use the principles as a shared language in retrospectives and governance forums.
	•	Over time, refer back: “We didn’t meet the alignment principle this sprint — that’s where we drifted.”
	5.	Reflect & Adapt
	•	Periodically review: are any principles being compromised silently?
	•	Use retros and process reviews to reinforce neglected principles.

Pro Tip: Post the eight principles visibly in war rooms or dashboards. Call them “your delivery north stars.”

